H0.text: Skeletal muscle fibers are the fibers along which myofibrils, long cylindrical structures, lie parallel to and run the entire length.

H1.text: Uplift muscle fibers are the fibers along which myofibrils lie parallel to and run the entire length.

H2.text: Luminous muscle fibers are the fibers along which myofibrils, long cylindrical structures, lie parallel to and run the entire length.

H3.text: Heart muscle fibers are the fibers that myofibrils, long cylindrical structures, lie parallel to and run the entire length of.

A4.text: The muscle cell is nearly filled with myofibrils running parallel to each other on the long axis of the cell.
